<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="25" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[151,1437,474,933]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,338,654,680]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[350,614,655,681]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctulata">
<emphasis box="[350,614,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Trachylepis punctulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from southwestern 
<collectingCountry box="[973,1055,655,681]" name="Angola" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Angola</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Marques, M. P. &amp; Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[1075,1324,655,681]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="1 - 501" refId="ref38562" refString="Marques, M. P., Ceriaco, L. M. P., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2018) Diversity and distribution of the amphibians and terrestrial reptiles of Angola atlas of historical and bibliographic records (1840 - 2017). Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 65 (Supplement 2), 1 - 501." type="journal article" year="2018">
Marques 
<emphasis box="[1188,1250,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="111 - 117" refId="ref37152" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1904) Reptis e amphibios de Angola da regiao ao norte do Quanza (Colleccao Newton 1903). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (25), 111 - 117." type="journal article" year="1904">Ferreira (1904</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, J. B." box="[231,288,691,718]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="159 - 171" refId="ref37198" refString="Ferreira, J. B. (1906) Algumas especies novas ou pouco conhecidas de amphibios e reptis de Angola (Coleccao Newton - 1903 - 1904). Jornal de Sciencias Mathematicas Physicas e Naturaes, Segunda Serie, 7 (26), 159 - 171." type="journal article" year="1906">1906</bibRefCitation>
) did not publish these specimens, however specimen MHNCUP/REP 278 was labeled as “ 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1862" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="acutilabris">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Trachylepis acutilabris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
”, a misidentification most likely made by himself. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ceriaco, L. M. P. &amp; De Sa, S. A. C. &amp; Bandeira, S. &amp; Valerio, H. &amp; Stanley, E. L. &amp; Kuhn, A. L. &amp; Marques, M. P. &amp; Vindum, J. V. &amp; Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[856,1104,727,754]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="15 - 61" refId="ref35490" refString="Ceriaco, L. M. P., De Sa, S. A. C., Bandeira, S., Valerio, H., Stanley, E. L., Kuhn, A. L., Marques, M. P., Vindum, J. V., Blackburn, D. C. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2016 a) Herpetological survey of the Iona National Park and Namibe National Park, Angola, with a synoptic list of the amphibians and reptiles of Namibe Province, southwestern Angola. Proceedings of the California Academy of Sciences, Series 4, 63 (2), 15 - 61." type="journal article" year="2016">
Ceríaco 
<emphasis box="[952,1009,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
(2016a)
</bibRefCitation>
cited the Newton Expedition specimens as congruent with their collections and commented that the locality “Mossamedes” most likely referred to 
<collectingRegion box="[180,377,799,825]" country="Angola" name="Namibe" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Namibe Province</collectingRegion>
as a whole, rather than the city. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[742,890,799,825]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctulata">
<emphasis box="[742,890,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">T. punctulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was, for a long time, considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Peters, 1870)" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[151,567,835,861]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[151,397,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">Trachylepis variegata</emphasis>
(Peters, 1870)
</taxonomicName>
, but a series of studies both on phylogeny and morphological characteristics have established the two taxa as different species (
<bibRefCitation author="Portik, D. M. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[727,971,871,897]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="128 - 142" refId="ref39209" refString="Portik, D. M. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2012) Untangling the complex: molecular patterns in Trachylepis variegata and T. punctulata (Reptilia: Scincidae). African Journal of Herpetology, 61 (2), 128 - 142. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 21564574.2012.721808" type="journal article" year="2012">Portik &amp; Bauer 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Bates, M. F. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Bauer, A. M. &amp; Burger, M. &amp; Marais, J. &amp; Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. S." box="[984,1181,871,897]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" refId="ref33732" refString="Bates, M. F., Branch, W. R., Bauer, A. M., Burger, M., Marais, J., Alexander, G. J. &amp; de Villiers, M. S. (2014) Atlas and Red List of the Reptiles of South Africa, Lesotho and Swaziland. Suricata 1. South African National Biodiversity Institute, Pretoria, xvii + 485 pp." type="book" year="2014">
Bates 
<emphasis box="[1054,1112,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Weinell, J. L. &amp; Branch, W. R. &amp; Colston, T. J. &amp; Jackman, T. R. &amp; Kuhn, A. &amp; Conradie, W. &amp; Bauer, A. M." box="[1201,1436,871,897]" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" pagination="183 - 195" refId="ref40781" refString="Weinell, J. L., Branch, W. R., Colston, T. J., Jackman, T. R., Kuhn, A., Conradie, W. &amp; Bauer, A. M. (2019) A species-level phylogeny of Trachylepis (Scincidae: Mabuyinae) provides insight into their reproductive mode evolution. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 136, 183 - 195. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2019.04.002" type="journal article" year="2019">
Weinell 
<emphasis box="[1296,1353,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
reported 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Bocage" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[251,399,907,933]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="punctulata">
<emphasis box="[251,399,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">T. punctulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as paraphyletic with respect to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1870" box="[753,888,907,932]" class="Reptilia" family="Scincidae" genus="Trachylepis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="24" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis box="[753,888,907,932]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="25">T. variegata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
